\b0 \
The data generated during analysis (the 694 key words for creativity and the 14 key components of creativity) are openly available online in the form of an ontology (also submitted as a supporting file), published under the URI {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://purl.org/creativity/ontology"}}{\fldrslt http://purl.org/creativity/ontology}} . As also stated in the paper, this data is made available under the Public Domain Dedication and License v1.0 whose full text can be found at: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.opendatacommons.org/licenses/pddl/1.0/"}}{\fldrslt http://www.opendatacommons.org/licenses/pddl/1.0/}} . This data is also available in the PhD thesis of Anna Jordanous (2012), which is openly available via the University of Sussex library ( {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://sro.sussex.ac.uk/44741/"}}{\fldrslt http://sro.sussex.ac.uk/44741/}} ) or via the University of Kent\'92s Academic Repository ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://kar.kent.ac.uk/42388/1/Jordanous%252C_Anna_Katerina.pdf"}}{\fldrslt https://kar.kent.ac.uk/42388/1/Jordanous%252C_Anna_Katerina.pdf}} ). \
\
90 academic publications dated 1950-2009 are analysed as part of this work. All of these articles were accessed via Scopus searches, through academic publishers. A full list of these publications is given in Jordanous\'92s thesis (available as per the links above) and the creativity corpus publications are listed in this article, in Figure 1. \
\
Data from the British National Corpus (BNC) was used during analysis. The BNC data is available from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.natcorp.ox.ac.uk/"}}{\fldrslt http://www.natcorp.ox.ac.uk/}} .\
\
The creativity Semantic Web ontology links to data from the Wordnet lexical database ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wordnet-rdf.princeton.edu/"}}{\fldrslt http://wordnet-rdf.princeton.edu/}}), via the openly available data published at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wordnet.rkbexplorer.com/"}}{\fldrslt http://wordnet.rkbexplorer.com/}} .}